						<p style="line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 11.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #777777; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">9.1.6 The Service Provider has the right to reject an instruction to perform a task in a certain way when a better or easier way can be done. The Service Provider will not mop the floor using their hands and cloth nor will they hand wash clothes no matter the reason. They however, can mop the floor with a mop and use the washing machine.</span></p>
